The article discusses the efforts of President Biden and Vice President Harris to protect voting rights in the United States. It highlights the challenges posed by state legislatures passing laws that make it harder to vote and recent Supreme Court rulings that have further hindered efforts to combat discrimination. The article mentions that President Biden and Vice President Harris have called on the Senate to pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act, and have even urged for changes to Senate rules to prevent a minority of Senators from blocking action to protect voting rights. The Biden-Harris Administration has also signed an executive order to promote access to voting and is working to implement initiatives to encourage electoral participation.